nts?\r\n\r\n\"Before I formed you in the belly I knew you; and before you came forth out of the womb I sanctified you, and I ordained you a prophet unto the nations\" (Jeremiah 1:5)  _\r\n\r\nOur Creator instructed the same prophet to confirm to us that He created us for good works that He has before ordained for us to fulfill. \"Call unto me, and I will answer you, and show you great and mighty things, which you know not.\" (Jeremiah 33:3)\r\n\r\nGod can do this because He is eternal. What does that mean? \"God is from everlasting to everlasting\" means God is an eternal being existing outside the constraints of time, having no beginning in the past and no end in the future. It means God is living in the Present Tense with Adam and Eve, at the same time, with Moses in Egypt, at the same time in Jerusalem with the Apostles and at the same time when the end of time occurs. \r\n\r\nGod is not limited by time, as humans are. He does not have a \"before\" or \"after,\" but exists in a perpetual \"now,\" often described as the great \"I AM\". He is the same yesterday, today, and forever. God is the author of creation and the one who has completed it. He exists at the beginning of time and at the same time, is there at the end of time. \r\n\r\nGod describes it this way through His prophet Isaiah 57:15, \u201cFor thus says the high and lofty One that inhabits eternity, whose name is Holy; I dwell in the high and holy place, with him also that is of a contrite and humble spirit, to revive the spirit of the humble, and to revive the heart of the contrite ones.\u201d\r\n\r\nSince God is inherently eternal, He is the source of eternal life and blessings to his people, which are described as being lasting and unconditional.\r\n", "author": "Come-mistertallyman", "created": 1777824506826, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "EstroTurf", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Did you know God knew all about you before even your parents?", "last_comment_created": 1777824891309, "content": "<p>Did you know God knew all about you before even your parents?</p>\n<p>&quot;Before I formed you in the belly I knew you; and before you came forth out of the womb I sanctified you, and I ordained you a prophet unto the nations&quot; (Jeremiah 1:5)  _</p>\n<p>Our Creator instructed the same prophet to confirm to us that He created us for good works that He has before ordained for us to fulfill. &quot;Call unto me, and I will answer you, and show you great and mighty things, which you know not.&quot; (Jeremiah 33:3)</p>\n<p>God can do this because He is eternal. What does that mean? &quot;God is from everlasting to everlasting&quot; means God is an eternal being existing outside the constraints of time, having no beginning in the past and no end in the future. It means God is living in the Present Tense with Adam and Eve, at the same time, with Moses in Egypt, at the same time in Jerusalem with the Apostles and at the same time when the end of time occurs.</p>\n<p>God is not limited by time, as humans are. He does not have a &quot;before&quot; or &quot;after,&quot; but exists in a perpetual &quot;now,&quot; often described as the great &quot;I AM&quot;. He is the same yesterday, today, and forever. God is the author of creation and the one who has completed it. He exists at the beginning of time and at the same time, is there at the end of time.</p>\n<p>God describes it this way through His prophet Isaiah 57:15, \u201cFor thus says the high and lofty One that inhabits eternity, whose name is Holy; I dwell in the high and holy place, with him also that is of a contrite and humble spirit, to revive the spirit of the humble, and to revive the heart of the contrite ones.\u201d</p>\n<p>Since God is inherently eternal, He is the source of eternal life and blessings to his people, which are described as being lasting and unconditional.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 10, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2050596676268618147", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZfAPPDm", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 83, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "sleepy", "id": 8596472, "raw_content": "", "author": "Hanging_Chad", "created": 1777782964586, "profile_picture": "GUPKlPiq0RXL", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "orcwordlaugh", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZfAPPDm.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/YossiBenYakar/status/2050596676268618147", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "\ud83c\udff4\udb40\udc67\udb40\udc62\udb40\udc65\udb40\udc6e\udb40\udc67\udb40\udc7f 30 officers were sent to arrest a mannequin, because it hurt Muslim feelings \ud802\udd82\ud81a\ude06\ud800\udc2a\ud81a\udc0b", "last_comment_created": 1777804640527, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 10, "score_up": 83, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 2757, "created": 1777735320000, "id": "2050596676268618147", "video